https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/16836689/158809721-3d1d1fd4-d367-418f-aab3-ee2fc7a748b8.mp4

 - The docs have a "Handling an unrecoverable state" section, but they only specify how to listen onto unrecoverable states, and not how to actually recover from them. So far I have tried:
 
 ```
  constructor(private swUpdate: SwUpdate) {
    swUpdate.unrecoverable.pipe(
      switchMap(() => {
        console.log('irrecoverable!');
        this.recover();
        return swUpdate.available;
      })
    ).subscribe(event => {
        swUpdate.activateUpdate().then(() => document.location.reload());
    });
  }

  public recover(): void {
    interval(1000).subscribe(() => {
      void this.swUpdate.checkForUpdate();
    });
  }
```

however the unrecoverable observable is not emmitting an event when the error happens.
